[assistant] You're right — that test was invalid for `commons-io:2.2`.
[assistant] 
[assistant] Cause:
[assistant] - In `2.2`, `ClassLoaderObjectInputStream.resolveClass(...)` does:
[assistant]   - `Class.forName(name, false, classLoader)`
[assistant]   - then only falls back if the returned class is `null`
[assistant] - But `Class.forName(...)` does not use `null` as a "not found" signal here; it throws `ClassNotFoundException` instead.
[assistant] - So the `line 75` fallback path is effectively unreachable in this version, and the `NullReturningClassLoader` test was forcing a failure, not valid coverage.
[assistant] 
[assistant] Fix applied:
